  <chapter number="1" style="c" sid="1PE 1" />
  <verse number="1" style="v" sid="1PE 1:1" />Petros, <char style="add">+an</char>_ambassador of_<char style="nd">Yaʸsous/(Yəhōshūˊa)</char> <char style="nd">chosen_one/messiah</char>, to_<char style="add">+the</char>_chosen aliens of_<char style="add">+the</char>_dispersion of_Pontos, Galatia, Kappadokia, Asia, and Bithunia, <verse eid="1PE 1:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="1PE 1:2" />according_to <char style="add">+the</char>_foreknowledge of_<char style="nd">god</char> <char style="add">+the</char>_father by <char style="add">+the</char>_holiness of_<char style="add">+the</char>_<char style="nd">spirit</char>, to <char style="add">+the</char>_obedience and sprinkling of_<char style="add">+the</char>_blood of_<char style="nd">Yaʸsous</char> <char style="nd">chosen_one</char>: grace to_you_all and might_have_multiplied peace. <verse eid="1PE 1:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="1PE 1:3" />Blessed <char style="add">=is</char> the <char style="nd">god</char> and father of_the <char style="nd">master</char> of_us, <char style="nd">Yaʸsous</char> <char style="nd">chosen_one</char>, who according_to the great mercy of_him, having_born_again us to <char style="add">+a</char>_ living _hope, through <char style="add">+the</char>_resurrection of_<char style="nd">Yaʸsous</char> <char style="nd">chosen_one</char> from <char style="add">+the</char>_dead, <verse eid="1PE 1:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="1PE 1:4" />to <char style="add">+an</char>_ indestructible _inheritance, and undefiled, and unfading, having_been_kept in <char style="add">+the</char>_heavens for you_all, <verse eid="1PE 1:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="1PE 1:5" />who by <char style="add">+the</char>_power of_<char style="nd">god</char> being_guarded through faith, for <char style="add">+the</char>_salvation ready to_be_revealed in <char style="add">+the</char>_ last _time. <verse eid="1PE 1:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="1PE 1:6" />In which you_all_are_exulting <char style="add">+a</char>_little now, if fitting having_been_sorrowed by various trials, <verse eid="1PE 1:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="1PE 1:7" />in_order_that the proving the faith of_you_all more_preciously <char style="add">=than</char> gold which <char style="add">=is</char> perishing, by but fire being_approved, may_be_found to praise, and glory, and honour, in <char style="add">+the</char>_revelation of_<char style="nd">Yaʸsous</char> <char style="nd">chosen_one</char>. <verse eid="1PE 1:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="1PE 1:8" />Whom you_all_are_loving not having_seen, in whom now not seeing but believing, you_all_are_exulting with_joy inexpressible and having_been_glorified, <verse eid="1PE 1:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="1PE 1:9" />receiving_back the outcome of_the faith of_you_all, <char style="add">+the</char>_salvation of_souls. <verse eid="1PE 1:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="1PE 1:10" />Concerning which salvation, <char style="add">+the</char>_prophets sought_out and searched_out, having_prophesied for the grace toward you_all, <verse eid="1PE 1:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="1PE 1:11" />searching into who or what time the <char style="nd">spirit</char> of_<char style="nd">chosen_one</char> in them was_making_evident, previously_testifying the sufferings for <char style="add">+the</char>_<char style="nd">chosen_one</char>, and the after these <char style="add">&gt;things</char> glories. <verse eid="1PE 1:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="1PE 1:12" />To_whom it_was_revealed that they_were_ not _serving unto_themselves, but unto_you_all <char style="add">+the</char>_same <char style="add">&gt;things</char>, which now was_declared to_you_all, by the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> having_good_message_preached to_you_all by_<char style="add">+the</char>_ holy _<char style="nd">spirit</char>, having_been_sent_out from heaven, into which <char style="add">&gt;things</char> angels are_desiring to_investigate. <verse eid="1PE 1:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="1PE 1:13" />Therefore having_girded_up the loins of_the mind of_you_all, being_sober, completely hope on the grace being_brought to_you_all at <char style="add">+the</char>_revelation of_<char style="nd">Yaʸsous</char> <char style="nd">chosen_one</char>. <verse eid="1PE 1:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="1PE 1:14" />As children of_obedience, not conforming to_the earlier desires in the ignorance of_you_all, <verse eid="1PE 1:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="1PE 1:15" />but as the <char style="add">&gt;one</char> having_called you_all holy, also let_ yourselves _become holy in all conduct, <verse eid="1PE 1:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="1PE 1:16" />because it_has_been_written, you_all_will_be: holy, because I <char style="add">=am</char> holy. <verse eid="1PE 1:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="1PE 1:17" />And if you_all_are_calling_on <char style="add">+the</char>_father, the <char style="add">&gt;one</char> impartially judging according_to the work of_each <char style="add">&gt;one</char>, be_conducted in fear the of_the sojourn time of_you_all, <verse eid="1PE 1:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="1PE 1:18" />having_known that you_all_were_redeemed not by_perishable <char style="add">&gt;things</char>, by_silver or by_gold, from the useless conduct of_you_all inherited_from_forefathers, <verse eid="1PE 1:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="1PE 1:19" />but by_<char style="add">+the</char>_precious blood, of_<char style="nd">chosen_one/messiah</char> as of_<char style="add">+a</char>_lamb unblemished and spotless, <verse eid="1PE 1:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="1PE 1:20" />having_been_foreknown on_one_hand before <char style="add">+the</char>_foundation of_<char style="add">+the</char>_world, on_the_other_hand having_been_revealed in <char style="add">+the</char>_last times because_of you_all, <verse eid="1PE 1:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="1PE 1:21" />who by him believing in <char style="nd">god</char>, the <char style="add">&gt;one</char> having_raised him from <char style="add">+the</char>_dead, and having_given glory to_him, so_as the faith and hope of_you_all, to_be in <char style="nd">god</char>. <verse eid="1PE 1:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="1PE 1:22" />Having_purified the souls of_you_all by obedience to_the truth in unhypocritical brotherly_love earnestly love one_another out_of heart. <verse eid="1PE 1:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="1PE 1:23" />Having_been_born_again, not of perishable but of_indestructible corruption by <char style="add">+the</char>_ living and remaining _message of_<char style="nd">god</char>. <verse eid="1PE 1:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="1PE 1:24" />Because: All flesh <char style="add">=is</char> like grass, and all <char style="add">+the</char>_glory of_it like <char style="add">+the</char>_flower of_grass. The Grass /Was/_withered, and the flower fell_from, <verse eid="1PE 1:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="1PE 1:25" />but the <char style="add">+the</char>_message of_<char style="add">+the</char>_<char style="nd">master</char> is_remaining to the age. And this is the message having_been_good_message_preached to you_all.<chapter eid="1PE 1" /><chapter number="2" style="c" sid="1PE 2" /><verse eid="1PE 1:25" /><verse number="1" style="v" sid="1PE 2:1" />Therefore having_put_away all malice, and all deceit, and hypocrisies, and envies, and all slanders, <verse eid="1PE 2:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="1PE 2:2" />like newborn babies long the logical unadulterated milk, in_order_that by it you_all_may_be_grown for salvation, <verse eid="1PE 2:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="1PE 2:3" />if you_all_tasted that the <char style="nd">master</char> <char style="add">=is</char> good. <verse eid="1PE 2:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="1PE 2:4" />To whom approaching <char style="add">+a</char>_ living _stone, on_one_hand having_been_rejected by humans, on_the_other_hand chosen by <char style="nd">god</char>, honoured, <verse eid="1PE 2:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="1PE 2:5" />also yourselves as living stones you_all_are_being_built, <char style="add">+a</char>_ spiritual _house, into <char style="add">+a</char>_ holy _priesthood to_offer_up spiritual sacrifices acceptable to_<char style="nd">god</char> through <char style="nd">Yaʸsous/(Yəhōshūˊa)</char> <char style="nd">chosen_one</char>. <verse eid="1PE 2:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="1PE 2:6" />Because it_is_contained in in_scripture: See I_am_laying <char style="add">+a</char>_stone in Siōn/(Tsiuōn), <char style="add">+a</char>_cornerstone chosen honoured, and the <char style="add">&gt;one</char> believing in him, by_no_means may_ not _be_disgraced. <verse eid="1PE 2:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="1PE 2:7" />Therefore <char style="add">=is</char> the value to_you_all, the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> believing, but to_disbelieving <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> <char style="add">+The</char>_stone which the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> building rejected, this was_become to <char style="add">+the</char>_head of_<char style="add">+the</char>_corner, <verse eid="1PE 2:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="1PE 2:8" />and: <char style="add">+A</char>_stone of_stumbling, and <char style="add">+a</char>_rock of_offense, who are_stumbling disbelieving in_the message, to which also they_were_appointed. <verse eid="1PE 2:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="1PE 2:9" />But you_all <char style="add">=are</char> <char style="add">+a</char>_ chosen _race: <char style="add">+a</char>_royal priesthood, <char style="add">+a</char>_ holy _nation, <char style="add">+a</char>_people for <char style="add">^his</char>_procuring, so_that the virtues you_all_may_proclaim_out, of_the <char style="add">&gt;one</char> having_called you_all out_of darkness, to the marvellous light of_him, <verse eid="1PE 2:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="1PE 2:10" />who once <char style="add">were</char> not <char style="add">+a</char>_people, but now <char style="add">=are</char> <char style="add">+the</char>_people of_<char style="nd">god</char>, the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> not having_been_shown_mercy, and now having_been_shown_mercy. <verse eid="1PE 2:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="1PE 2:11" />Beloved, I_am_exhorting as sojourners and aliens, to_be_keeping_away from_the fleshly desires, which are_warring against your soul, <verse eid="1PE 2:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="1PE 2:12" />having the good conduct of_you_all among the pagans, in_order_that at which they_are_slandering against_you_all as of_evildoers, by observing your good works, they_may_glorify <char style="nd">god</char> in <char style="add">+the</char>_day of_visitation. <verse eid="1PE 2:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="1PE 2:13" />Be_subjected to_every human creation because_of the <char style="nd">master</char>, whether to_<char style="add">+the</char>_king as being_above, <verse eid="1PE 2:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="1PE 2:14" />or to_governors as being_sent by him, for vengeance to_evildoers, but praise to_welldoers. <verse eid="1PE 2:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="1PE 2:15" />Because thus is the will of_<char style="nd">god</char>, doing_good to_be_silencing the ignorance of_foolish people., <verse eid="1PE 2:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="1PE 2:16" />as free <char style="add">live</char>, and not having the freedom as <char style="add">+a</char>_cover-up of_the evil, but as slaves of_<char style="nd">god</char>. <verse eid="1PE 2:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="1PE 2:17" />Honor all, be_loving the brotherhood, be_revering <char style="nd">god</char>, be_honouring the king. <verse eid="1PE 2:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="1PE 2:18" />house_servants, being_subjected with all respect to_your masters, not only to_the good and gentle, but also to_the crooked. <verse eid="1PE 2:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="1PE 2:19" />For this <char style="add">+a</char>_favour <char style="add">=is</char>, if because_of conscience of_<char style="nd">god</char>, anyone is_bearing_under sorrows suffering unjustly. <verse eid="1PE 2:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="1PE 2:20" />For what credit <char style="add">is_it</char>, if sinning and being_beaten you_all_will_be_enduring <char style="add">it</char>? But if doing_good and suffering you_all_will_be_enduring <char style="add">it</char>, this <char style="add">=is</char> <char style="add">+a</char>_favour before <char style="nd">god</char>. <verse eid="1PE 2:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="1PE 2:21" />For you_all_were_called to this, because <char style="nd">chosen_one/messiah</char> also suffered for you_all, leaving <char style="add">+an</char>_example to_you_all, in_order_that you_all_may_follow_after after_the steps of_him, <verse eid="1PE 2:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="1PE 2:22" />who neither did sin, nor was_ deceit _found in the mouth of_him, <verse eid="1PE 2:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="1PE 2:23" />who being_insulted, was_ not _retaliating, suffering, was_ not _threatening, but was_giving_over <char style="add"> him</char> to_the <char style="add">&gt;one</char> judging justly, <verse eid="1PE 2:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="1PE 2:24" />who himself offered_up the sins of_us in the body of_him on the stake, in_order_that having_died to_sins, we_may_live to_righteousness, of_whose by_his wounds you_all_were_healed. <verse eid="1PE 2:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="1PE 2:25" />For you_all_were like sheep being_strayed, but you_all_were_returned now to the shepherd and overseer of_the souls of_you_all.<chapter eid="1PE 2" /><chapter number="3" style="c" sid="1PE 3" /><verse eid="1PE 2:25" /><verse number="1" style="v" sid="1PE 3:1" />Likewise, women, being_subjected to_your own husbands, in_order_that even if any are_disbelieving in_the message, they_will_be_being_won by the conduct of_their wives apart_from message, <verse eid="1PE 3:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="1PE 3:2" />having_observed the pure conduct in respect of_you_all. <verse eid="1PE 3:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="1PE 3:3" />Of_whom it_let_be not the <char style="add">person</char> outwardly of_braid of_hairs and of_putting_about of_gold or adorning of_dresses of_clothes, <verse eid="1PE 3:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="1PE 3:4" />but the hidden person of_the heart, in the indestructible <char style="add">beauty</char> of_the gentle and quiet spirit, which is precious before <char style="nd">god</char>. <verse eid="1PE 3:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="1PE 3:5" />For thus once also the holy women hoping in <char style="nd">god</char> were_adorning themselves, being_subjected to_their own husbands, <verse eid="1PE 3:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="1PE 3:6" />as Sarra/(Sārāh) submitted to_Abraʼam/(ʼAvərāhām): calling him master, of_whom you_all_were_become children, doing_good and not fearing not_one fear. <verse eid="1PE 3:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="1PE 3:7" />men, likewise dwelling_with <char style="add">them</char> according_to knowledge, as with_<char style="add">+a</char>_weaker vessel with_the feminine, rendering_out honour as also to_fellow-heirs of_<char style="add">+the</char>_grace of_life, in_order that the prayers of_you_all to_ not _be_being_hindered. <verse eid="1PE 3:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="1PE 3:8" />And the end, all <char style="add">being</char>, like_minded, sympathetic, brother-loving, tender-hearted, humble, <verse eid="1PE 3:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="1PE 3:9" />not giving_back evil for evil, or insult for insult, but instead blessing, that to this you_all_were_called, in_order_that you_all_may_inherit blessing. <verse eid="1PE 3:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="1PE 3:10" />For the <char style="add">&gt;one</char> wanting life to_be_loving, and to_see good days, let_ his tongue _cease from evil, and <char style="add">^his</char>_lips not to_speak deceit. <verse eid="1PE 3:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="1PE 3:11" />And let_him_turn_away from evil, and let_him_do good, let_him_seek peace and let_him_pursue it. <verse eid="1PE 3:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="1PE 3:12" />Because <char style="add">+the</char>_eyes of_<char style="add">+the</char>_<char style="nd">master</char> <char style="add">=are</char> on <char style="add">+the</char>_righteous, and <char style="add">+the</char>_ears of_him toward <char style="add">+the</char>_petition of_them, but <char style="add">+the</char>_face of_<char style="add">+the</char>_<char style="nd">master</char> <char style="add">=is</char> against those_doing evil. <verse eid="1PE 3:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="1PE 3:13" />And who <char style="add">=is</char> the <char style="add">&gt;one</char> going_to_mistreat you_all, if you_all_may_become zealous for_the good? <verse eid="1PE 3:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="1PE 3:14" />But if even might_be_suffering because_of righteousness, <char style="add">you_are</char> blessed. And the fear of_them, neither be_afraid nor you_all_may_be_disturbed, <verse eid="1PE 3:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="1PE 3:15" />But as_<char style="nd">master</char> the <char style="nd">chosen_one/messiah</char> sanctify in the hearts of_you_all, always <char style="add">be</char> ready for <char style="add">+a</char>_defense to_everyone requesting you_all <char style="add">+an</char>_account, concerning the hope in you_all, <verse eid="1PE 3:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="1PE 3:16" />but with gentleness and respect, having <char style="add">+a</char>_ good _conscience, in_order_that in which they_are_slandering of_you_all as evildoers, the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> mistreating of_you_all may_be_disgraced the good conduct in <char style="nd">chosen_one</char>. <verse eid="1PE 3:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="1PE 3:17" />For <char style="add">it_is</char> better to_be_suffering doing_good, if the will of_<char style="nd">god</char> might_be_willing <char style="add">it</char>, than doing_evil. <verse eid="1PE 3:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="1PE 3:18" />Because also <char style="nd">chosen_one</char> died_off once for <char style="add">+the</char>_sins for of_us <char style="add">+the</char>_righteous for <char style="add">+the</char>_unrighteous, in_order_that he_may_bringing_forward you_all to_<char style="nd">god</char>, on_one_hand having_been_put_to_death in_<char style="add">+the</char>_flesh, on_the_other_hand having_been_given_life in_<char style="add">+the</char>_<char style="nd">spirit</char>, <verse eid="1PE 3:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="1PE 3:19" />in which also having_been_gone to_the to_spirits in prison he_proclaimed, <verse eid="1PE 3:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="1PE 3:20" />to_having_disbelieved <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> once when the patience of_<char style="nd">god</char> was_eagerly_waiting in <char style="add">+the</char>_days of_Nōe/(Noḩa), <char style="add">+the</char>_ark being_prepared in which <char style="add">+a</char>_few, this is, eight souls, were_brought_safely_through through <char style="add">+the</char>_water. <verse eid="1PE 3:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="1PE 3:21" />Which also representative now <char style="add">+the</char>_immersion is_saving you_all, not <char style="add">+a</char>_removal of_<char style="add">+the</char>_filth of_flesh, but of_<char style="add">+a</char>_ good _conscience, <char style="add">+the</char>_inquiry toward <char style="nd">god</char> through <char style="add">+the</char>_resurrection of_<char style="nd">Yaʸsous/(Yəhōshūˊa)</char> <char style="nd">chosen_one</char>, <verse eid="1PE 3:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="1PE 3:22" />having_been_gone into heaven who is at <char style="add">+the</char>_right <char style="add">hand</char> of_<char style="nd">god</char>, with_angels, and authorities, and powers having_been_subjected to_him.<chapter eid="1PE 3" /><chapter number="4" style="c" sid="1PE 4" /><verse eid="1PE 3:22" /><verse number="1" style="v" sid="1PE 4:1" />Therefore <char style="nd">chosen_one</char> having_suffered in_<char style="add">+the</char>_flesh, also you_all arm the same intention, because the <char style="add">&gt;one</char> having_suffered in_<char style="add">+the</char>_flesh has_ceased from_sin, <verse eid="1PE 4:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="1PE 4:2" />in_order that to_live the remaining time in <char style="add">+the</char>_flesh no_longer to_lusts of_<char style="add">+the</char>_people, but to_<char style="add">+the</char>_will of_<char style="nd">god</char>. <verse eid="1PE 4:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="1PE 4:3" />For the having_passed_by time <char style="add">=is</char> sufficient to_have_produced the counsel of_the pagans, having_pursued in wantonness, lusts, drunkenness, carousing, drinking_parties, and unlawful idolatries. <verse eid="1PE 4:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="1PE 4:4" />With which they_are_being_surprised, not running_together of_you_all into the same of_intemperance pouring_out, slandering, <verse eid="1PE 4:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="1PE 4:5" />who will_be_giving_back <char style="add">+an</char>_account to_the <char style="add">&gt;one</char> ready to_judge <char style="add">+the</char>_living and <char style="add">+the</char>_dead. <verse eid="1PE 4:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="1PE 4:6" />For to this <char style="add">end</char> was_good_message_preached even to_<char style="add">+the</char>_dead, in_order_that they_may_be_judged on_one_hand according_to humans in_<char style="add">+the</char>_flesh, on_the_other_hand may_be_living according_to <char style="nd">god</char> in_<char style="add">+the</char>_spirit. <verse eid="1PE 4:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="1PE 4:7" />And the end of_all has_neared. Therefore be_sensible and be_sober for <char style="add">+the</char>_prayers, <verse eid="1PE 4:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="1PE 4:8" />before all <char style="add">&gt;things</char>, having the earnest love among yourselves, because love is_covering <char style="add">+a</char>_multitude of_sins, <verse eid="1PE 4:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="1PE 4:9" /><char style="add">be</char> hospitable to one_another apart_from grumbling, <verse eid="1PE 4:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="1PE 4:10" />each <char style="add">&gt;one</char> as he_received <char style="add">+a</char>_gift, serving it to yourselves, as good managers of_<char style="add">+the</char>_various grace of_<char style="nd">god</char>. <verse eid="1PE 4:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="1PE 4:11" />If anyone is_speaking, as oracles of_<char style="nd">god</char>, if anyone is_serving, as of strength of_which <char style="nd">god</char> is_supplying, in_order_that in all <char style="add">&gt;things</char> <char style="nd">god</char> may_be_being_glorified through <char style="nd">Yaʸsous</char> <char style="nd">chosen_one/messiah</char>, to_whom is the glory and the power to the ages of_the ages. Truly. <verse eid="1PE 4:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="1PE 4:12" />Beloved, be_ not _being_surprised at_the fiery_trial among you_all for trial to_you_all becoming, as_though of_<char style="add">+a</char>_stranger happening to_you_all, <verse eid="1PE 4:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="1PE 4:13" />but as you_all_are_sharing in_the sufferings of_the <char style="nd">chosen_one</char>, be_rejoicing in_order_that you_all_may_be_elated also exulting in the revelation of_the glory of_him. <verse eid="1PE 4:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="1PE 4:14" /><char style="add">You_are</char> blessed if you_all_are_being_derided in <char style="add">+the</char>_name of_<char style="nd">chosen_one</char>, because the the <char style="nd">spirit</char> of_the of_glory and of_<char style="nd">god</char>, is_resting on you_all. <verse eid="1PE 4:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="1PE 4:15" />For not let_ anyone _be_suffering of_you_all as <char style="add">+a</char>_murderer, or <char style="add">+a</char>_thief, or <char style="add">+an</char>_evildoer, or as <char style="add">+a</char>_meddler. <verse eid="1PE 4:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="1PE 4:16" />But if as <char style="add">+a</char>_follower_of_the_messiah, not let_him_be_being_ashamed, but let_him_be_glorifying <char style="nd">god</char> in this name. <verse eid="1PE 4:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="1PE 4:17" />Because the time <char style="add">it_is</char> to_begin the judgment from the house of_<char style="nd">god</char>, and if first from us, what <char style="add">will_be</char> the outcome of_the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> disbelieving in_the good_message of_<char style="nd">god</char>? <verse eid="1PE 4:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="1PE 4:18" />And if the righteous is_being_saved with_difficulty, where will_be_appearing the ungodly and sinner? <verse eid="1PE 4:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="1PE 4:19" />So_then also the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> suffering according_to the will of_<char style="nd">god</char>, let_them_be_entrusting the souls of_them to_<char style="add">+a</char>_faithful creator in welldoing.<chapter eid="1PE 4" /><chapter number="5" style="c" sid="1PE 5" /><verse eid="1PE 4:19" /><verse number="1" style="v" sid="1PE 5:1" />Therefore I_am_exhorting elders among you_all, <char style="add">+a</char>_fellow-elder and witness of_the sufferings of_the <char style="nd">chosen_one</char>, also the partner of_the glory going to_be_being_revealed, <verse eid="1PE 5:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="1PE 5:2" />shepherd the flock of_<char style="nd">god</char> among you_all, not compulsory, but willingly, according_to <char style="nd">god</char>, not greedily, but eagerly, <verse eid="1PE 5:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="1PE 5:3" />not as exercising_mastership over_<char style="add">+the</char>_lots, but becoming examples to_the flock. <verse eid="1PE 5:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="1PE 5:4" />And the chief_shepherd having_been_revealed, you_all_will_be_receiving_back the unfading crown of_glory. <verse eid="1PE 5:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="1PE 5:5" />Likewise, younger <char style="add">&gt;ones</char>, be_subjected to_<char style="add">^your</char>_elders. And, all tie_in humility to_one_another because, <char style="nd">god</char> is_opposing against_<char style="add">+the</char>_proud, but is_giving grace to_<char style="add">+the</char>_humble <char style="add">&gt;ones</char>. <verse eid="1PE 5:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="1PE 5:6" />Therefore be_humbled under the mighty hand of_<char style="nd">god</char>, in_order_that he_may_exalt you_all in time, <verse eid="1PE 5:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="1PE 5:7" />having_throw_on all the worry of_you_all on him, because with_him is_caring about you_all. <verse eid="1PE 5:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="1PE 5:8" />Be_sober, watch. The opponent of_you_all, <char style="add">+the</char>_devil, is_walking as <char style="add">+a</char>_lion roaring, seeking to_swallow_up, <verse eid="1PE 5:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="1PE 5:9" />against_whom resist, solid in_the in_faith, having_known the same <char style="add">&gt;things</char> of_the sufferings, by_the in the world of_you_all brotherhood you_all_are_experiencing. <verse eid="1PE 5:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="1PE 5:10" />And the <char style="nd">god</char> of_all grace, the <char style="add">&gt;one</char> having_called you_all to the eternal glory of_him in <char style="nd">chosen_one/messiah</char>, you_having_suffered little, he will_be_preparing <char style="add">you</char>, will_be_strengthening <char style="add">you</char>, will_be_strengthening <char style="add">you</char>, <verse eid="1PE 5:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="1PE 5:11" />to_him <char style="add">be</char> the dominion for the ages. Of_the ages. Truly. <verse eid="1PE 5:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="1PE 5:12" />By Silouanos, I_wrote to_you_all of_the faithful brother (as I_am_reckoning), through short <char style="add">messages</char>, exhorting and testifying this to_be <char style="add">+the</char>_true grace of_<char style="nd">god</char>, in which you_all_stood. <verse eid="1PE 5:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="1PE 5:13" />Is_greeting you_all the in Babulōn/(Bāvel?) chosen_together, and Markos, the son of_me. <verse eid="1PE 5:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="1PE 5:14" />Greet one_another with <char style="add">+a</char>_kiss of_love. Peace <char style="add">be</char> to_you_all all, who <char style="add">=are</char> in <char style="nd">chosen_one</char>.<chapter eid="1PE 5" /></usx>